---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <Nav />

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6">
      Find what's already been built.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-body leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-2xl">
      A community registry for AI tools. Discover who's working on similar problems. Keep the incentives that make building worthwhile.
    </p>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-5">
      <a href="/explore" class="px-5 py-2.5 bg-emphasis font-medium text-sm rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity" style="color: #ffffff;">
        Explore the registry
      </a>
      <a href="/submit" class="text-sm text-emphasis hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
        Submit a tool
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-rule">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-8">The origin</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5 text-body leading-relaxed">
      <p>In 1997, Garry Kasparov lost to Deep Blue. His response wasn't to stop playing chess. It was to invent a new kind — advanced chess, where human and machine play together.</p>
      <p>The team that won wasn't the best human or the best machine. It was the best partnership. We call that a centaur.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-rule my-12"></div>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-body leading-relaxed">
      <p>The AI tools moment feels like that. Builders everywhere. Discoveries daily. The energy is real and the work is extraordinary. But spend time in the channels where this work happens and you'll notice something: the room is full and somehow also empty.</p>
      <p>Everyone broadcasts. Nobody accumulates. Two nearly equivalent tools appear in consecutive messages and nobody asks: how do these differ? What does one do that the other doesn't? Wouldn't it be something if someone built the version that had both?</p>
      <p>The signal that could become knowledge never quite gets there — because there's nowhere for it to happen. This is that place.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-rule">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-10">How it works</h2>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Provenance</h3>
        <p class="text-body">Every tool carries its lineage. Related projects link to each other. When work overlaps, both builders know.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Proximity</h3>
        <p class="text-body">Submit a tool, meet your neighbors. The registry matches on the problem you're solving and introduces you to others working in the same space.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">One rule</h3>
        <p class="text-body">MIT license. Everything on centaur.tools is forkable, stealable, buildable-upon. The only social contract is: cite your parents.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-rule">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-4">The tools are here. The builders are here.</h2>
    <p class="text-body mb-8">centaur.tools is where they meet.</p>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-5">
      <a href="/explore" class="px-5 py-2.5 bg-emphasis font-medium text-sm rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity" style="color: #ffffff;">
        Explore the registry
      </a>
      <a href="/submit" class="text-sm text-emphasis hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
        Submit a tool
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
